caption: This place is unquestionably one of the finest place to eat in the region. Always when I visit this place I am extremely satisfied. They hold their very high  standard service and the topmost level of meals  they offer. You are always happy with this restaurant. Warmly  recommended.

This spot is my preferred one. I visit a lot of restaurants but to this restaurant I go the most. The crew is very professional and the food they place on your table is so yummy. I would always prefer to have a good dinner here. I highly recommend this place.

This is by far one of the cutest places in DC for a quick bite and coffee! The staff was amazing and seemed very familiar with their customers. The owner was there when I dropped by she was so nice and patient with my order...I had my two little indecisive ones with me. The food was great and the drinks were PERFECT! if you're ever around you must drop in the decor alone is worth it !!!
What great place for beer and pretzels! What an awesome staff. Thank you!

The food was great and there were lots of draft beer options. The pretzels were hot and fresh with an excellent cheese spread. Lots of authentic German food and of course sausages! Due to COVID, the ambience was not the most desirable, but still the host tried their best. Will definitely go back!
This restaurant is first-rate and broad, the meals was enchanting and the prices were very inexpensive. quick, productive service and very affable waiters. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
Always delicious. Even though Covid restrictions necessitated eating outside, they had ambient space heaters at each table. Very comfortable. Great service.
Awesome food, helpful employees, regularly excellent atmosphere. They charge fair pricing and the food quality is great. Great work.
Decent german 🍻 bar. Service is painfully slow and food is a tad bit expensive than other similar bars around dc
Awesome little spot! Service was a tad slow but worth the wait.
Old staple on Capitol Hill. Love having a German beer on their patio.

Worst experience at a restaurant that I’ve had my entire life. We are trying to support small businesses and we regret doing this just because of our experience at Cafe Berlin. They better issue an explanation for the 3+ hour wait we had to endure to pick up food that we ordered since the 9th of December outside in a line that wrapped around the block in the rain and cold. They had elderly people waiting in that line disregarding their order and their needs. Even after we were first in line, they still took 45 min to bring us cold containers of food that were far from the amount of money we paid for. Worst food quality and service service I’ve experience from a restaurant that is supposed to sell the whole German experience.

CAN’T PREPARE FOOD ON TIME. We paid over $125 for a pre-ordered Christmas dinner & had to wait outside for nearly 2 hours for pick-up (in the pouring rain). Never ordering a meal from here again, that’s for sure!

I love this spot! They serve splendid food, their menu is rich, The cook in that restaurant is a real pro, I love a lot eating all their dishes. The dishes are consistently fresh, the service towards the visitors  is good. I  go often to this place and I was never unhappy.  I highly recommend it.
Really excellent food and great German beer. Apple strudel is worth coming for alone! Nice outside area with heaters and parasols that are surprisingly warm even for December.
Liked the food,  great atmosphere.  Roladen seems to be a special dish. I guess call in advance if you're looking to order it.  Not always served.
Oh man, this place has some awesome German sandwiches. I used to come here a lot for lunch and they had the best sandwiches. Great place some German bier as well.

Outdoor dining was great! Heaters and blankets provided. And as usual the food and wine were excellent, served by an attentive but not intrusive staff! Five star quality at very reasonable prices!

We enjoy going out. Yesterday we came to this fine restaurant which friends told us about. We had a beautiful evening there with great meal and  an experienced stuff and a distinguished  chef. We  added this venue in our list  and we shall certainly return very soon. We deeply recommend.

Went here for a birthday lunch with my friend and it was good. There are absolutely no bad things I can say about it, but there was nothing that really made incredible. Everything was very good: the food, the service, the location, the overall feel. However nothing made me feel like it was something that is just amazing.
Quaint, quiet, and cozy. Great food and drinks!

I went for an Oktoberfest pig roast. It included 1L of beer, a plate of roast pork & 2 sides, and a warm apple strudel for $55. The food was excellent, but I had expected a little more pork. I'd give it 4.5 stars if I could. We also got appetizers. The currywurst was really nice. It's a weisswurst with curry seasoning & sauce. The pretzels with beer cheese were a little disappointing--the beer cheese was camambert-based, and was too bland for the pretzels, which were also under-salted. Total for the meal for 2 w/ appetizers and 2 extra liters of beer was $182 + tip.  Covid-19 precautions: everyone is required to wear a mask when they aren't eating or drinking. Menus are disposable. Tables indoors are 8-10ft apart, and outdoor tables are around 5-6ft apart. There are also air filters in every room, but I'm not sure those air filters are effective against covid-19.
Authentic everything
Great outdoor ambiance, good food and loved the beer.
Would definitely recommend trying this place. Excellent mood, delicious food, excellent customer service. They never disappoint.

Dined here a few times preCOVID. Fairly good food. Walked by yesterday before 5pm and saw that about half the patio tables outside were in use but was turned away due to expected reservations with nothing free until 830 pm. A mystery with so many empty tables. I was told I could dine inside. Indoors the restaurant is very small with tight spaces. Why restaurants think anyone wants to dine inside during COVID times I have no idea. All I wanted was a beer but no luck. Nothing impromptu on this desolate area of Mass Ave on a beautiful Fall afternoon during COVID times.
German style Wienerschintzel, the bratkartoffel was pretty good too!
It’s just always so good. Amazing patio too.
If you make a reservation make sure you get a table IN the garden and not in the garden LEVEL in between the gas meter and the trash bins. Good German food and beer though.

Great staff and great food.  The braised beef is definitely my favorite here as well as the cod.  However the beer is also a draw... So really get the beer and the beef and you will go home happy.  The staff is extremely responsive and cordial.  Definitely coming back!
We had a wonderful dinner on the outdoor patio.
Best food Ive had in the longest time! Surpassed my expectations!!!
Would surely recommend visiting this place. Great character, delightful food, fantastic customer service. Fantastic work.

Am a huge fan of German food and beverage.  The menu was scaled down due to the current virus situation.  Had jagrrschnitzel and it was delicious.  The sour kraut balls were very tasty.  A great dining experience.
Took advantage of a Sunday meal deal for pick up along with a growler of my favorite Hefeweisen. We've loved this place for many years, and even more during the pandemic.
Fabulous.  Service attentive and sweet.  Patio nicely covered. Food scrumptious and just the correct amount.  We celebrated my friend's birthday very well.  Thanks for opening
Pricey, but definitely one of the better schnitzels I've had. Outdoor dine-in seating now available.

My husband and I loved, loved this restaurant...we ate there several times on last trip to D.C. to see Pope Francis...the food, staff and biers and schnapps ...all excellent...sadly my husband passed away 8 months ago and now I am gong thru chemo....Cafe Berlin will be on my bucket list, God willing.....Thanks for the wonderful memories,,,from Texas❤

We came to this spot for lunch. we heard about this spot from many people.  Well, it was very successful. we were warmly welcomed by the crew  and we felt fantastic. The meal was delicious. We enjoyed every moment and we shall definitely come back again. Keep it up.

I tried this place once with my friend and I am addicted ever since. I love the good vibes and flavorful food and drinks. Kudos.

At the moment  you arrive in this place  they give you an agreeable feeling. Very congenial hosts, it is a lovely restaurant to go out with buddies or with your date. tasty  food, skillful  chef, competitive  cost and excellent  service. Warmly recommended.
Very nice place to dine. Food was great

Cafe Berlin is one of the few remaining restaurants in DC that serve German cuisine. Schnitzel, wurst, they gave it all. Plus, an excellent rotating German draft selection.
I've been here a number of times and the food is always great. The staff is friendly and helpful. Cozy atmosphere inside and great outdoor seating for when it's nice out. Highly recommend.
This was our end of the year "first" to a new restaurant and it did not disappoint. The service was fantastic, atmosphere warm, and the food was great.
Great place for Christmas Day dinner. Their cocktails are delicious and reasonably priced. The sauerbraten and goose are wonderful. Make a reservation for 2020.
The food here was very good.  It's a bit crowded, not Handicap Accessible but we made it with a collapsible walker.

Been meaning to pop in there since I moved, finally a cold rainy night was perfect for some warm German meals.  Warm, cozy inside the feel of small family places I went to in New Jersey and NYC.  The 4 german salads did not match the menu description and were a hit and miss.  Cucumber memories of my grandmother making it, the reset were not to our liking, but very easily could be to others.  The potato pancakes on point. My grandmother use more minced onion, just saying. :)  I consumed all of my Jagerschnitzel, but would have been happy with any of the schnitzels.  The wild boar goulasch was so rich, part of it came home with us. Desserts again the gooseberry a miss with the gelatin like consistency but the pear tart on point.  See you all again soon.
Amazing food!

Love this place! The food is among the best in town, with traditional German dishes and a bit of creativity splashed here and there. Autumn is a great time with Oktoberfest followed by their Wild Game Menu in November. I’ve had a few of the plates and can’t say enough about them!

Not recommended when you know German taste. We had the Wiener schnitzel but it wasn’t good. It seems the 2 staff ladies have an Problem to work together. Atmosphere isn’t great. Beer was good but expensive.
You will recognize old favorites but be surprised and pleased by the updates. The patio is always lovely and inside is cozy. Leave room for dessert.
Came here during my lunch break and was very disappointed. The food was good but really overpriced for what you get. I think the rude service made it overall a disappointing experience.
Food was excellent! Great place to eat would highly recommend!

The food is delicious and the beers are 👌.  Prices are a bit high but for a night out this is a fantastic spot to enjoy an evening with friends or family.

Great German food. Large selection of beers. Casual fun atmosphere. Great patio. Entrance not immediately visible but stick with it. Large part of Germans eating at the next table. Always a good sign.

Pleasant Bier Garten atmosphere, especially in the garden at night. Good beer selection on tap and delicious Bavarian style dishes. The Wurst platter is excellent. Get the potato salad and sauerkraut with it. Also the mushroom and potato dumpling (Schupfenudeln?) is heavenly.
Great place if you're looking for German food and lots of beer!

This is German food reimagined with new fresh ingredients and beautiful plating. You will recognize old favorites but be surprised and pleased by the updates. The patio is always lovely and inside is cozy. Leave room for dessert.

I had a great experience at Cafe Berlin this afternoon. My Wiener Schnitzel was the best I've had and the selection of beers is great.  This is an authentic German restaurant that has earned a great reputation. Thank you!

Great German food in the Bavarian tradition and Keller bier on tap!  I am thrilled to have a true Bavarian kitchen here in DC, the food takes me back!
The schnitzel sandwich and goulash were terrific, as was the chocolate chip cheesecake (Zupfkuchen), and Amy was a fabulous server. Loved the whole experience. I shall be back.
My family and I had an amazing experience here. The food was amazing. The service was amazing. I highly recommend that eat here.
I needed reliably fresh, healthy and delicious lunch option and i found it. Staff was very friendly and helpful. A bit pricey for me but I can live with it.

I love having the ability to travel and see how others perceive our food and culture. This was very close to what I grew up eating. The foods are popular in Berlin and other regions too (Currywurst is beloved throughout the entire country and is prepared with different Würste). Prices are middle-range (8 to 25+USD). For DC, this is pretty cheap. My poor partner and his family did not know what they got themselves into! If you are unsure about German food, try the Bretzl/Bretzel (Soft Pretzel), Currywurst (in this case, a Bratwurst with curry ketchup), or a platter of Würste.
An authentic and outstanding German restaurant. The food is fresh the waitstaff knowledgeable and quick. Highly recommend the bratwurst and the beer.
Verrrry nice food.. The beer is super good..
Great authentic German foods!
Great!
The food was excellent and delicious.

We happened upon this place because we needed a quick bite before dropping our friend off at Union station. We literally parked on the street and this gem was across the street so in we went.  The hostess inside was quick to greet us and to see us. Surprisingly this restaurant spans three small buildings there. It is very tight quarters and the bathrooms are quite small but the decor is quaint and elegant and even though everyone sits somewhat close together the decorations and drapes between side table/booths help give you a sense of privacy. The prices were decent, burger was $14, steak sandwich was $20, and bacon omelette was $12(?).  They seem to have a wine cellar up front and their brunch drink prices were good also (Bellini for $8)  I would visit this neat little gem again.

I can’t say enough good things about this restaurant.  The food and atmosphere are authentic and the owners are a very nice German and American couple.  If you were ever posted in Germany and miss the Schnitzel, wursts and beer then this is definitely a restaurant to visit.

Always solid! The food is better at Mozart, but the beer is better here. Solid choice for convenience, atmosphere, berating owners, constantly changing staff, neighborhood- middle-aged-hooligans, and most importantly...completely edible food. Rare hill gem.
Food is amazing. Really loved it. Only thing, try to rearrange the umbrellas to better cover the patio.

Had high hopes for the Cafe Berlin and with early reservations we were seated quickly and offered drinks but then the service just went downhill from there. Although there were only 4 others in our section a small group (of about 8) came into the other section next to us and all attention immediately went there. Despite being seated right next to the door between the two rooms our server dashed by us multiple times but treated us as if we were invisible. We were never even asked how the meal was or if we needed anything else. Needing a new knife the only way we could get one was to take it off the place setting at the table next to us. My wife asked if our server could take a photo but we were told he was too busy and could not. Clearly his only interest was working for the big tip he was hopeful for from the group and our business was unimportant.  Food was ok but nothing special or even really memorable. A different person did take our check quickly...Funny how even when service is subpar they can always take your money quickly and that 'service' element always shines.. In a city with a lot of great dining options this would not be a place I'd recommend or return to. Disappointing.

The owner is rude. I have been a regular customer for the last nine years and even brought my family for Christmas and Easter meals. Today was my last day coming. The owner, Mrs. Roberts-Glage is rude. Did I disturb her, playing with the kid behind the bar? Well, there was nobody else around. Why was she so upset? After the meal, I went inside to speak with her, to give her a second chance. Nope. No way. Madam, you are in a wrong business.
Loved the atmosphere, loved the food and service.
I've always enjoyed dining here, however it's finally time for me to leave a review.  Good food, good service, and some seriously strong kaffee!  Stop by and you'll most certainly be back.

The beer is of course delicious and the prices probably for the area in the immediate vicinity of Capitol Hill, etc. also very good. We definitely recommend it. Seriously delicious food. Traditional German fare, schnitzel, sauerbraten, you name it. Plenty of German beer on tap, as well as wine. Special expanded menu for Oktoberfest as well. Asked by friends to join them for dinner as they had been here before. I looked at the menu before we went. Saw a few things I thought I'd like.  Had reservations so we were seated right away and the hostess that took us to our table could not have been any nicer! If only the experience would have stayed that way. Our waitress came to take our drink orders as we were talking about which beer or wine to get and instead of being helpful and recommending drinks, she walked away. Didn't say a word just went to another table. We didn't see her again for 10 minutes! When she finally did come back we ordered drinks and our food for fear she wouldn't come back for another 10 minutes. Our food came out and we all agreed it was good but nothing to keep us coming back. I most definitely enjoyed the German version of cheese cake for dessert...it was very good!

Cafe Berlin is the most authentic German restaurant in the DC area. Even my dad, who is a professionally-trained German chef, raves about how good the food is, saying it reminds him of eating in his hometown. The waiter humored my attempts at ordering in German, while having a full conversation with my father. The food is authentic and delicious, the beer is directly from the source, and the atmosphere is a delight.

Apalling rudeness! I am a 35+ year veteran of the restaurant business and a 25+ year customer of Cafe Berlin. In my (extensive ) experience it doesn't take more than 10 minutes to flip a tablecolth. I will never give this establishment more business 😡

Great experience in the US. My wife is German, and we lived in Chicago, so it was very pleasant for both of us to eat german, it was like home ! Thank you for the food, but also for the service which was excellent !

Fantastic German Beer Selection - my pick Rothaus . Amazing Spätzle , that according to their menu and on web page are made from scratch as is anything else on the menu. Which you can tell but wanted to point out. Although the menu is mainly meat dishes , the first time I went I had veggie Maultaschen ( stuffed pasta ), which had been amazing too. Seating is available in the garden or I their dinning Room. Which has that authentic german living room feeling of a restaurant in Germany.

This was an absolutely wonderful experience. I am originally from East Germany, came here when I was 4. I have lived in the United States for the last 29 years. Honestly, today, my English is better than my German. But it was wonderful to go to a place where at least a few of the staff members spoke German. I was able to have small talk and place my order in German. The atmosphere was wonderful. They have an excellent selection of wine, and foods that are very very authentic. I could not believe myself. I will most definitely be going back. If I had a word to describe it: ausgezeichnet!

If you want authentic traditional German food this is the place to go. The real deal! Quaint outdoor  dining patio on Mass ave. Good selection of German beers and the food is outstanding.  Sauerbraten was amazing.
Wonderful food, great service!!
Real German Restaurant for me. Awesome Schnitzel ever in DC

Great outdoor seating and the food was very Herman and spectacular. If you don’t get here early enough for a World Cup game you may have to stand or be aggressive enough to ask someone to share their table. I had their farmers egg dish. ‘Twas amazing. Beer selection is very good as well.

Awesome German dining experience. We took my brother in law here for his birthday.  I'm a fan of any place you can order a litter of beer. The food was classic German, but with a kind of upscale twist. We each got an appetizer and entree, and no one was disappointed.  If you are looking for a place to get some good food and beer, look no further.

The food here is great. There is a chef in that kitchen, a real chef. Service is always very good. It's not super fancy; it is a garden level space, but the patio is excellent when it's warm. Traditional German dishes and often new ideas from the chef based on seasonal produce.
Not fancy but good food

It was okay, the service was good, but the food underwhelming. As a former EU citizen, can definitely not say it was truly authentic.

Choose inside seating because terrace was 1/2hr wait. Inside only 20% full but still waited 30 Min get our drinks. Food was good but everyone service was terrible. Table next to us asked if they got free drinks for waiting so long but then thought no - by time free drinks arrive they might be leaving. Food was actually pretty good but such a long wait killed our happiness with the food. We ordered 2nd drink to have with the meal but by time 2nd round came, food was cold!
Quaint with a progressive feel. Delicious spot conveniently close to Union Station. Couldn't have asked for better weather for the outdoor seating; not sure what they do in the winter.
Outstanding place for a reception. Clytie enabled us to greet the mourners after my sister's funeral and the hospitality of Cafe Berlin helped turn a sad day into a joyful one.

Great food and service.
Delicious authentic German food - perhaps the best in the city. Our waiter was knowledgeable about all the dishes, cordial, and professional.

Just finished a quick lunch here. Thoroughly satisfied. Everything from the decor to the service to the house corned beef on my reuben was stellar. Will be stopping by this classic German-themed gem every time I'm in DC.
The Reuben is the best Reuben in DC hands down. As my waiter said "straight from God's table"

Great German Food owned and operated by a German Chef and American spouse. Upscale food but with friendly, home style environment. Great attentive staff and open for Lunch, Brunch and Dinner. Find famous Capital Hill governments, DC tourists, and regulars often.
I always enjoy their schnitzel. Unfortunately, the Arnold Palmer I had was incredibly bland.

Wonderful staff. I wish we lived in DC so we could eat there once or twice a month. The sauerbraten was very tasty, made from the chuck, but it suffered a little from being served in stewing-sized chunks. I think they should rather serve it sliced on a bias. Did I say wonderful staff? Well, they are.

Very good food and HUGE beers for a good price. They have several holiday options as well. Reservations not needed but also not a bad idea. The options for dessert are also great. The authenticity is not found anywhere else. Good wait staff.
Delicious food and a wonderful selection of beers! Can't wait to go back!
I usually don’t like German food even tho I’m German but I loved the food here and it was a great experience

Exceptional food, especially for a neighborhood where drinking is more prominent in the establishment.  The portions and prices are also well above par.  And, there are several authentic menu items unique to the place.  I recommend the Sauerkraut balls for starters.  The only disappointment was that service was slow -- but friendly.  We got the impression that several of the team were new.  We had a great time, so the delays were inconsequential, but don't plan for anything fast.
One of my favorite places on Capitol Hill!
Outstanding German restaurant.  The wurst plate enough to share and delicious pork medallions.
Great service, great authentic german cuisine, great german beer selection, cozy atmosphere
A DC institution. Awesome German food and superb service but not at all hauty or snobby. Been coming for over 25 years. Excellent lunch or dinner choice.

Can't claim to know much about German cuisine, but I brought my aunt and uncle who were visiting from overseas just to try it together. We got some great recommendations from our server, and the servings were more than enough. We made a reservation through OpenTable and were seated promptly upon arrival, and never waited too long for anything.

Had a great Christmas dinner with family. Food was delicious and three of us had leftovers there was so much! Excellent price. Nice beer list and server took the time to explain the seasonal drafts. Server told us they all work as a team so feel free to speak to anyone for service which we did so there wasn't a problem in that regard. We will be back!

Once again, an excellent meal in a cozy setting. Service was great. Selection good. The temperature in the restaurant was a little cool, due to the outside temps.  Nice and quiet setting. Really enjoyed it.
Great food and atmospher

An amazing meal with excellent prices for the area.  The food quality is amazing, their selection is authentic.  Parking may be a challenge but not to worry, easy to get to from Union Station.  Be sure to call and make reservations,  they have a smaller dining room which might seat 30 to 40.  Can't wait to get back there.
Good German food but very limited menu. I try to avoid gluten and just about every dish had gluten. German Potato salad was very bland.
Great food..

This is a quaint little place in a good location near the Library of Congress. I can't profess to be an expert on German cuisine, but I'd like to think I can tell when something is made fresh versus from a can or is made using shortcuts.  My girlfriend and I decided to just do appetizers as we had an important dinner later that day. We ordered the mac and cheese, schnitzel, soup, potato dumpling, and potato pancakes.  My favorite was the potato dumpling. Interestingly it had the texture of sticky rice but in potato form and was served in a pool of beef gravy. The gravy was very potent and tasted like stock broth from a jar, but very good!  The pancakes were also good and are basically hash browns (luckily I like hash browns) and served with apple sauce and a pumpkin butter. Never had that combination before but it was extremely tasty.  The other two either lacked flavor (mac and cheese) or were too damn good to be legally sold. But again I could taste the shortcuts and enough of them made me feel a little disappointed.
Cozy restaurant average food
Love this place. Good quality, nice atmosphere,. A family favorite for German food.
Phenomenal food, good beer, and excellent service
Always good. I'll let it didn't have my rose cider last time, maybe next time.

Fantastic, attentive, friendly service and excellent food. Beautiful patio seating too!

I was SEVERELY dissapointed with my visit here for the Oktoberfest Saturday. We had a reservation at 1:30pm and when we walked in, we were in happy spirits and excited to be there. We walked out frustrated, upset and disrespected after waiting half an hr. When we were greeted, the server was rude and told us "it will be a while"....well we had a reservation and why was she being rude to us about our reservation? Then we waited 30 mins where we seemed to be in the way and grumpy servers rushing past. Finally two seats at the bar opened and we seated ourselves. The bartender was not friendly at all and then when we went to order, they had already run out of the suckling pig "Spanferkel"...which is the reason we had come.  Not only that but the bartender was SUPER rude, unwelcoming, mean and down right I WILL NEVER visit this establishment again. No reason to be this rude. Especially when I was so excited to eat one of my favorite German meals.
